# Documentation Guidelines

## Structure
- Documentation is organized in the `docs/` directory
- Blog posts are stored in the `blog/` directory
- Sidebar navigation is configured in [sidebars.ts](mdc:sidebars.ts)

## Markdown Features
- Use standard Markdown syntax
- Support for MDX (JSX in Markdown)
- Can import and use React components
- Code blocks with syntax highlighting

## Configuration
Documentation settings are managed in [docusaurus.config.ts](mdc:docusaurus.config.ts):
- Site metadata
- Navigation structure
- Theme configuration
- Plugin settings

## Best Practices
- Use clear hierarchical structure
- Include code examples where relevant
- Leverage Docusaurus features like admonitions
- Keep documentation up-to-date with code changes
